WEBVTT

00:05.539 --> 00:08.607
[ Clinking, rustling ]

00:13.414 --> 00:16.081
Two months suspended vacation
with pay.

00:16.083 --> 00:17.383
This is absurd.

00:17.385 --> 00:18.751
There are worse things.
Like what?

00:18.753 --> 00:21.120
Two months suspended
<i>without</i> pay.

00:21.122 --> 00:24.089
And all because you let that kid
follow you around all night?

00:24.091 --> 00:26.091
Well, they said
I should have called c.F.S.

00:26.093 --> 00:28.210
Why didn't you?

00:28.211 --> 00:30.328
Well, he's a good kid
who was worried about his mom.

00:30.331 --> 00:31.463
You're a good man.

00:31.465 --> 00:32.798
That's where I'll be.
Ooh.

00:32.800 --> 00:37.636
First I got to spend
a whole shift with Gina perello,

00:37.638 --> 00:39.438
the hag they're sending
to run this place...

00:39.440 --> 00:40.640
[ Knocking ]
While I'm gone.

00:40.641 --> 00:41.807
[ Clears throat ]
Dr. Taylor?

00:41.809 --> 00:42.809
Who the hell are you?

00:42.810 --> 00:44.276
The hag.

00:49.116 --> 00:51.183
[ Telephones ringing ]

00:53.220 --> 00:55.120
Yah!

00:55.122 --> 00:56.122
Where's my wife?

00:56.123 --> 00:57.623
[ Grunts ]
Where's my son?

00:57.625 --> 00:59.458
Frank,
you have to try not to move.

00:59.460 --> 01:01.493
I told him
I didn't want to go first.

01:01.495 --> 01:03.328
[ Whimpers ]
Where's my family?

01:03.330 --> 01:04.330
E.T.A.?

01:04.331 --> 01:05.597
Three minutes out.

01:05.599 --> 01:06.899
Mr. Irving?

01:06.900 --> 01:08.200
They'll be here soon,
but you need to calm down.

01:08.202 --> 01:10.602
I told them
not to take me first.

01:10.604 --> 01:11.770
What do we have?

01:11.772 --> 01:13.172
Jesse:
I've called the O.R.

01:13.174 --> 01:15.574
Guthrie junior
is on his way down.

01:15.576 --> 01:17.309
Did they say what's coming in?

01:17.311 --> 01:19.111
No, just be out here, stat.

01:19.113 --> 01:21.113
[ Sirens wailing ]

01:21.115 --> 01:22.681
[ Police radio chatter ]

01:22.683 --> 01:23.683
Police escort?

01:23.684 --> 01:25.417
[ Tires screech ]
Whoa.

01:26.420 --> 01:27.286
What is it?

01:27.288 --> 01:28.687
It's a home invasion.

01:28.689 --> 01:30.289
This is the mom and the son now.

01:30.291 --> 01:31.457
Father's in center stage.

01:31.459 --> 01:32.758
Jesse:
Vitals are stable.

01:32.760 --> 01:34.159
10 of morphine, please.

01:34.161 --> 01:36.562
[ Frank gasps ]
Wow.

01:36.564 --> 01:38.597
The knife barely missed
his heart.

01:38.598 --> 01:40.631
Miracle he made it here without
perforating the pericardium.

01:40.634 --> 01:42.868
We have them to thank for that.

01:42.869 --> 01:45.309
Nobody here wants to leave until
they see this family survive.

01:46.640 --> 01:48.474
Let's stabilize the knife
and transport upstairs.

01:48.476 --> 01:50.142
We don't need it nicking
a vessel en route.

01:50.144 --> 01:51.577
Aah!
Paramedic:
17-year-old male.

01:51.579 --> 01:52.811
20-foot fall.
Deformity to left foot.

01:52.813 --> 01:54.046
Probable hip dislocation.

01:54.047 --> 01:55.280
Multiple bruises
and lacerations to his face.

01:55.282 --> 01:56.415
Fell from where?

01:56.416 --> 01:57.549
Jumped from the second story.

01:57.551 --> 01:58.884
Aah!

01:58.886 --> 02:00.752
Paramedic #2:
42-year-old female.

02:00.754 --> 02:03.455
15-centimeter full-thickness
laceration involving muscle

02:03.457 --> 02:05.124
to the right proximal arm.
Pete?!

02:05.126 --> 02:07.259
Mom!
Mom, are you okay?!

02:07.261 --> 02:08.827
I'm okay, I'm okay!

02:08.829 --> 02:10.145
Wait, wait, wait, mom!

02:10.146 --> 02:11.462
Pete!
Your mom's in good hands, son.

02:11.465 --> 02:13.165
We got to get you inside.

02:13.167 --> 02:14.522
How's my father?
Please!

02:14.523 --> 02:15.878
Your father's inside.
I don't know his status.

02:15.879 --> 02:17.234
This kid pulled himself by his
arms to the neighbor's house.

02:17.238 --> 02:18.471
He saved them all.

02:18.472 --> 02:19.705
Please tell me
that frank is alive.

02:19.707 --> 02:22.241
Okay, when we move him,
let's move him nice and easy.

02:22.243 --> 02:23.408
No bumps, people.
No bumps.

02:23.410 --> 02:24.476
[ Groans ]

02:24.478 --> 02:26.211
Pete!
Is that my father?

02:26.213 --> 02:27.246
Oh, my God!

02:27.248 --> 02:27.913
Frank, please don't move.

02:27.915 --> 02:29.248
Is my son okay?

02:29.250 --> 02:30.282
They're taking good care of him.

02:30.284 --> 02:31.216
Karen?!

02:31.218 --> 02:33.218
I'm okay.
I'm okay.

02:33.220 --> 02:34.937
Oh, frank!

02:34.938 --> 02:36.655
She's not attached.
On me. One, two, three.

02:36.657 --> 02:38.223
[ Groans ]

02:38.225 --> 02:39.591
Trauma labs, please?

02:39.592 --> 02:40.958
Cole: Two, three.
Move him now.
Aah!

02:40.959 --> 02:42.325
Guthrie: Jesse, gonna need
a portable X-Ray over here.

02:42.329 --> 02:43.428
Flying in.

02:43.430 --> 02:45.731
[ Groaning ]

02:45.733 --> 02:48.200
Son, stay still.
You've got a dislocated hip.

02:48.202 --> 02:49.351
Karen: Pete!

02:49.352 --> 02:50.501
Dr. Leighton,
pulse-check that leg.

02:50.504 --> 02:51.603
[ Pete groaning ]

02:51.605 --> 02:52.938
I've got a pulse here.

02:52.940 --> 02:54.239
I don't have a pulse down here.

02:54.241 --> 02:55.340
Damn it.
What does that mean?

02:55.342 --> 02:58.277
[ Pete groaning ]

02:58.279 --> 02:59.778
Go.
Clear. Shoot it.

02:59.780 --> 03:01.246
[ Beeping ]
[ Groaning ]

03:01.248 --> 03:02.614
Cole: Okay,
we're moving him now.

03:02.616 --> 03:05.350
Leanne: Careful.

03:05.352 --> 03:06.518
But...

03:06.520 --> 03:08.220
Mom! Please let me
see them first.

03:08.222 --> 03:09.588
No time.
We have to move.

03:09.590 --> 03:10.756
Let them see each other.

03:10.758 --> 03:11.924
This is not your patient.
There's no time.

03:11.926 --> 03:13.492
There<i> is</i> time.

03:13.494 --> 03:16.595
Frank,
turn your head very slowly.

03:16.597 --> 03:18.363
Okay?
Ugh.

03:18.365 --> 03:20.232
[ Groaning ]

03:20.234 --> 03:22.301
[ Grunts ]

03:24.305 --> 03:26.238
I... I love you.

03:26.240 --> 03:27.206
Dad, I love you.

03:27.208 --> 03:29.508
You saved us, kiddo.

03:29.510 --> 03:31.243
We're gonna be okay now.

03:31.245 --> 03:32.511
I love you both.

03:32.513 --> 03:34.379
Slowly.
Okay, slowly, let's go.

03:34.381 --> 03:35.447
Whoa!

03:35.449 --> 03:37.482
[ Monitor alarms beeping ]

03:37.484 --> 03:39.318
Damn it!
What's happening?

03:39.320 --> 03:40.642
I don't have a pulse!

03:40.643 --> 03:41.965
Okay, Dr. Pineda,
start compressions.

03:41.966 --> 03:43.288
Back, back, back.
Coming in, coming in.

03:43.290 --> 03:44.723
Gown up, gown up.
Frank?!

03:47.795 --> 03:49.394
What's happening to my father?

03:50.297 --> 03:51.797
Someone say something!

03:54.668 --> 03:55.801
You're gonna do that down here?

03:55.803 --> 03:57.403
We have no choice now.

03:57.404 --> 03:59.004
Pulseless in the e.D.
We have to explore the wound.

03:59.006 --> 04:01.406
May be a thoracic injury.

04:01.408 --> 04:02.975
Jesse.

04:02.977 --> 04:05.244
¶¶

04:12.353 --> 04:13.836
Okay, we should do this now.

04:13.837 --> 04:15.320
Pete, your hip was
knocked out of its socket

04:15.322 --> 04:16.538
when you jumped, all right?

04:16.539 --> 04:17.755
We're gonna have
to straighten it.

04:17.758 --> 04:18.857
Karen: Is that... is that
gonna hurt him?

04:18.859 --> 04:20.259
We'll give him some medication.

04:20.260 --> 04:21.660
Mario, can you help
over there, please?
Mario: Line in.

04:21.662 --> 04:23.962
Amy, 7 amphetamine.
Yes, doctor.

04:23.964 --> 04:26.331
[ Groans ]
Okay, everybody ready?

04:26.333 --> 04:27.399
One...

04:27.401 --> 04:28.600
Mom, mom, I'm scared.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.035
Two...
Shh, shh.

04:30.037 --> 04:31.336
Three.

04:31.338 --> 04:33.639
[ Popping ]
[ Screaming ]

04:35.009 --> 04:37.442
[ Groaning ]

04:37.444 --> 04:39.011
[ Crying ]

04:48.989 --> 04:51.023
Pete: Which one's dead?

04:51.025 --> 04:52.958
One of the medics said
that you killed one.

04:52.960 --> 04:55.794
Was it the big guy
or the small guy?

04:55.795 --> 04:58.629
Sir, can we wait until
my husband is out
of surgery to do this?

04:58.632 --> 05:00.565
Well, I have to get
a statement, ma'am.

05:00.567 --> 05:03.035
The big guy.
The small one was in custody.

05:03.037 --> 05:06.071
The big guy was the one
with the gun.

05:06.073 --> 05:08.006
The one who separated us.

05:08.007 --> 05:09.940
Doctor, is... is... is he okay
to be interviewed like this?

05:09.943 --> 05:11.543
Dr. Leighton
signed off on it.

05:11.545 --> 05:13.078
Now, you said
you were separated.

05:13.080 --> 05:15.047
Is that how you ended up
upstairs?

05:15.049 --> 05:16.581
Yeah.
Upstairs bathroom.

05:16.583 --> 05:18.383
Can you walk me through
what happened?

05:18.385 --> 05:20.018
He tied my wrists and ankles
with rope.

05:20.020 --> 05:23.455
Then he slammed my head
into the mirror.

05:23.457 --> 05:25.991
He said to stay put, and I did.

05:28.028 --> 05:29.361
For a long time.

05:31.398 --> 05:34.099
Too long.
I... I waited for too long.

05:34.101 --> 05:36.835
If I had just jumped earlier...

05:36.837 --> 05:38.470
It's all my fault.

05:38.472 --> 05:40.939
All your fault?!

05:40.941 --> 05:42.774
Pete, you saved us.

05:42.776 --> 05:44.576
If I had jumped sooner,
dad would have never been...

05:44.578 --> 05:47.012
Stop.
Stop it right now.

05:47.014 --> 05:50.849
Your mom's right, son.
You're a hero.

05:50.851 --> 05:52.984
I think it's a good time
for a break, don't you?

05:52.986 --> 05:54.920
Yeah.
I'll come back.

05:59.927 --> 06:01.860
You're younger than I expected.

06:01.862 --> 06:03.829
Vitamin "c" cream and exercise.

06:03.831 --> 06:08.133
I tried exercise once.
It didn't take.

06:08.135 --> 06:09.401
Look, I know you're worried

06:09.402 --> 06:10.668
that I'm gonna
burn this place down,

06:10.671 --> 06:12.888
but I know the job.

06:12.889 --> 06:15.106
I did it in sacramento last year
when they booted their guy.

06:15.109 --> 06:17.042
I wasn't booted.
Paid leave.

06:17.044 --> 06:18.710
Well,
to-may-to, to-mah-to.

06:18.712 --> 06:20.746
The point is, don't worry.

06:20.747 --> 06:22.781
I'm gonna take good care
of the place till you get back.

06:22.783 --> 06:25.384
Why does the board like you
so much?

06:25.386 --> 06:26.485
Handies.

06:29.390 --> 06:32.157
Mba from Yale,
Columbia med school,

06:32.159 --> 06:33.625
and admin training at mass gen.

06:33.627 --> 06:35.244
You had me at "handies."

06:35.245 --> 06:36.862
Angus: What do we have here?
Officer: 27-year-old male.

06:36.864 --> 06:39.631
Good pupil reactivity,
intoxicated and unconscious.

06:39.633 --> 06:41.099
Officer #2: On his way
to his wedding in Mexico,

06:41.101 --> 06:43.902
this idiot and five of his
friends got drunk at the airport

06:43.904 --> 06:45.036
and got thrown off their flight.

06:45.038 --> 06:45.871
Where are the others?

06:45.873 --> 06:47.072
Jail, except for this one.

06:47.074 --> 06:48.907
I have a stronger constitution.

06:48.909 --> 06:51.143
Impressive.
Has he had anything else?

06:51.145 --> 06:52.911
Just Tequila.
We screwed up.

06:52.913 --> 06:54.413
You think?

06:54.414 --> 06:55.914
Ooh.
I can smell him from here.

06:55.916 --> 06:59.084
Hello. I'm Dr. perello,
director of the E.R.

06:59.086 --> 07:01.052
Officers, why don't you
head to the break room,

07:01.054 --> 07:02.988
have some coffee...
Where is the break room?

07:02.990 --> 07:05.090
Uh, before you go, are these
restraints really necessary?

07:05.092 --> 07:06.491
Sir, step back, please.

07:06.493 --> 07:07.993
Why should I?

07:07.995 --> 07:08.860
Ugh!

07:08.862 --> 07:09.862
That's why.
That's why.

07:11.198 --> 07:12.531
Bathroom?

07:13.700 --> 07:17.536
Dr. perello, uh,
say hello to...

07:17.538 --> 07:19.638
Two of our fine...

07:19.640 --> 07:20.839
Still don't know our names.

07:20.841 --> 07:22.073
You're Dr. Leighton,
right?

07:22.075 --> 07:23.175
Yeah.
The nepotist.

07:23.177 --> 07:24.843
Nepotist?
Relax, I'm kidding.

07:24.845 --> 07:27.179
Well, half-kidding.
Your father is on the board.
Heh.

07:27.181 --> 07:28.980
And you're Dr. Lorenson?
Mm-hmm.

07:28.982 --> 07:30.482
You two go to the bathroom
together too?

07:30.484 --> 07:32.017
Excuse me?
Well, I was just wondering

07:32.019 --> 07:34.186
why I've got two residents
on one drunk.

07:35.189 --> 07:37.088
Divide and conquer.

07:37.090 --> 07:39.224
Continue the tour?

07:42.896 --> 07:45.130
Uh, was the bleeding
accompanied by pain?

07:45.132 --> 07:46.765
Mali:
He had a sore throat,

07:46.767 --> 07:49.501
so he's been on vocal rest
for the past week.

07:49.503 --> 07:50.135
Until today.

07:50.137 --> 07:51.503
No singing at all?

07:51.505 --> 07:53.705
Mnh-mnh.
No singing and no speaking.

07:53.707 --> 07:56.007
It's common practice
among performers.

07:56.009 --> 07:57.809
A lot of writing notes.

07:57.810 --> 07:59.610
Why did he sing today?
Was the sore throat gone?

07:59.613 --> 08:02.647
They are in rehearsals for
a very special performance

08:02.649 --> 08:05.750
for the presidents of south
Africa and the United States

08:05.752 --> 08:07.085
at Walt Disney concert hall.

08:07.087 --> 08:09.988
I read about that.
You're in "the lion king"?

08:09.990 --> 08:12.791
In the touring company, yes.

08:12.793 --> 08:15.160
He is mufasa.

08:15.162 --> 08:16.162
Oh.

08:18.065 --> 08:20.232
Dr. Pineda,
do you have a diagnosis yet?

08:20.234 --> 08:22.000
It's hard to see
through the swelling.

08:22.002 --> 08:23.535
We'll need a C.T. scan.

08:23.537 --> 08:26.204
I believe there's an abscess
in your throat.

08:26.206 --> 08:28.940
It's like a balloon
filled with fluid.

08:28.942 --> 08:30.876
Can you make him better?

08:33.013 --> 08:35.547
We'll know more
after we take some pictures.

08:35.549 --> 08:39.651
Uh, Dr. Pineda, never wait
for a test to form an opinion.

08:39.653 --> 08:41.219
Machines don't
diagnose patients.

08:41.221 --> 08:43.655
<i>We</i> do.

08:43.657 --> 08:46.124
Cole: Now I'm gonna
slowly pull the knife out

08:46.126 --> 08:49.728
<i>while you return the ligament
to its place.</i>

08:49.730 --> 08:51.663
<i>Watch for the nerve.
Suction.</i>

08:51.665 --> 08:53.298
[ Beep ]
Hey.

08:53.300 --> 08:54.199
How's he doing?

08:54.201 --> 08:56.001
He's well-trained.

08:56.003 --> 08:57.536
Doesn't waste a step.

08:57.538 --> 08:59.838
I meant the patient.

08:59.840 --> 09:01.973
Of course.
[ Chuckles ]

09:01.975 --> 09:04.643
That knife tore him up
pretty good.

09:04.645 --> 09:07.212
Sounds like it hit the spleen,
a lung,

09:07.214 --> 09:08.747
and the top of the liver.

09:08.749 --> 09:10.715
It's a miracle
he's alive at all.

09:18.825 --> 09:22.127
Tell me something, leanne.

09:22.129 --> 09:23.795
How did you
break through to Cole?

09:23.797 --> 09:25.213
What do you mean?

09:25.214 --> 09:26.630
Well, you seem to have made
a connection.

09:26.633 --> 09:28.333
We don't have a connection.

09:28.335 --> 09:30.168
Well, I can see he likes you.

09:33.840 --> 09:37.309
I really want this
to work out for him, leanne.

09:37.311 --> 09:39.311
I just...

09:39.313 --> 09:41.746
I'm just trying
to find a way in.

09:41.748 --> 09:44.249
I thought maybe you had
some advice for me.

09:44.251 --> 09:47.652
I wish I could help you,
rollie, but...

09:47.654 --> 09:49.821
Other than
a working relationship,

09:49.823 --> 09:51.923
I don't really know him at all.

09:56.964 --> 09:59.364
[ Door closes ]

09:59.366 --> 10:02.267
68-year-old male
with metastatic melanoma.

10:02.269 --> 10:04.269
Had chemo today.
Found down at home by his son.

10:04.271 --> 10:08.940
Low b.P... 87/58.
Temp 100.8, pulse is thready.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.141
Dad?
I'm right here, okay?

10:10.143 --> 10:11.977
Neal: Gonna need you over here,
Dr. Lorenson.

10:11.979 --> 10:13.278
Let's get him to bed 7.

10:14.314 --> 10:17.015
On my count.
One, two, three.

10:17.017 --> 10:18.683
Be... be careful.
He has dementia.

10:18.685 --> 10:20.352
He freaks easily.
Got it.

10:20.354 --> 10:22.120
We'll take care of him.

10:23.690 --> 10:26.725
Dr. Lorenson,
walk me through this.

10:26.727 --> 10:29.995
Airway's intact.
Pulse weak and thready.

10:29.997 --> 10:32.864
Breath sounds.

10:32.866 --> 10:35.367
Diffuse crackles throughout.

10:35.369 --> 10:37.969
Cap refill poorly perfused.

10:37.971 --> 10:40.271
Probable sepsis pneumonia.

10:40.273 --> 10:42.040
What's his fluid status?

10:42.042 --> 10:45.343
I.V.C. Collapsed.
He's extremely dehydrated.

10:45.345 --> 10:46.745
No access.
Veins are flat.

10:46.747 --> 10:48.603
What's your plan?

10:48.604 --> 10:50.460
[ Monitor alarms beeping ]
Quickly... b.P. Is dropping.

10:50.461 --> 10:52.317
Sepsis protocol... fluids,
broad-spectrum antibiotics.

10:52.319 --> 10:53.852
Pressors if it gets that far.

10:53.854 --> 10:54.854
Good. Next.

10:54.855 --> 10:57.122
2 liters wide open
into each I.V.

10:57.124 --> 10:58.023
Levophed ready to go, please.

10:58.025 --> 10:59.391
You got it, doctor.

11:01.028 --> 11:01.860
Is he okay?

11:01.862 --> 11:03.928
[ Beeping continues ]

11:07.200 --> 11:08.667
[ Beeping stops ]

11:08.669 --> 11:09.668
Blood pressure's improving.

11:09.670 --> 11:10.670
He's stable.

11:15.308 --> 11:17.075
[ Laughs ]

11:17.076 --> 11:18.843
Lawrence walked right into
the orchestra seats,

11:18.845 --> 11:22.313
took the girl's cell phone,
and kept right on singing.

11:22.315 --> 11:25.283
[ Laughter ]
Nathan: He just tossed it right
to Phil, that new hyena.

11:25.285 --> 11:27.452
That was the first casualty
of their stampede.

11:27.454 --> 11:29.721
[ Laughter ]

11:30.457 --> 11:33.158
Hi, everyone.
I'm Dr. Rorish.

11:33.160 --> 11:35.927
Sorry, but we normally don't
allow more than one visitor

11:35.929 --> 11:37.179
in trauma 1.

11:37.180 --> 11:38.430
These are Lawrence's castmates.

11:38.432 --> 11:39.964
I understand, but it's policy.

11:39.966 --> 11:41.332
Do you mind waiting outside,
please?

11:41.334 --> 11:42.434
Yes.
Yes, of course.

11:42.436 --> 11:44.469
Lawrence,
we'll be right outside. Yep.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.272
Thanks.

11:49.042 --> 11:56.181
Mr. falls, you have
a large peritonsillar abscess.

11:56.183 --> 11:58.983
It's a severe infection
deep inside your throat.

11:58.985 --> 12:03.254
And the swelling of it has
spread to the vocal cords.

12:03.256 --> 12:04.422
Is there medication
you can give him?

12:04.424 --> 12:06.391
Steroids and antibiotics
will help,

12:06.393 --> 12:08.093
but it needs to be drained.

12:08.095 --> 12:09.227
And will that fix it?

12:09.229 --> 12:11.730
It's the only way
to stop the infection.

12:11.732 --> 12:16.000
We won't know about your voice
for a couple of hours.

12:16.002 --> 12:17.402
But, Lawrence, you need
to understand that this

12:17.404 --> 12:19.404
is an extremely delicate
procedure.

12:19.406 --> 12:24.743
The abscess is wedged
between the vocal cords
and the carotid artery,

12:24.745 --> 12:26.945
which is the main source
of blood to the brain.

12:26.947 --> 12:29.214
[ Sighs ]
What does that mean?

12:29.216 --> 12:32.150
Think of it
like... like a raisin

12:32.152 --> 12:34.085
inside a peanut-butter
sandwich.

12:34.087 --> 12:37.222
We need to get the needle
inside the raisin.

12:37.224 --> 12:39.991
But the trick is, we can't
touch the peanut butter.

12:39.993 --> 12:40.859
No.
[ Grunts ]

12:40.861 --> 12:42.127
Please, Lawrence.

12:42.128 --> 12:43.394
The problem is
there's not much time.

12:43.396 --> 12:45.830
The abscess could burst
at any moment,

12:45.832 --> 12:48.133
flooding the throat
with infection.

12:48.135 --> 12:53.037
Lawrence, I understand you're
worried about losing your voice.

12:53.039 --> 12:55.473
But it's my first job to make
sure you don't lose your life.

12:58.311 --> 13:01.412
For my husband,
they are one and the same.

13:04.317 --> 13:07.152
[ Indistinct talking ]

13:08.822 --> 13:12.190
Man: [ Over P.A. ]<i> Triage nurse</i>
<i>to overflow nursing station.</i>

13:12.192 --> 13:14.993
<i>Triage nurse
to overflow nursing station.</i>

13:14.995 --> 13:18.096
Hi, I'm Dr. Leighton,
and you are...

13:18.098 --> 13:20.165
Rachel, Aaron's fiancée.
Is he sober yet?

13:20.167 --> 13:21.332
He's sleeping it off.

13:21.334 --> 13:23.101
Rachel, I told you...
He's gonna be fine.

13:23.103 --> 13:25.103
Shut up. I don't even know
why you're here.

13:25.105 --> 13:26.538
He's not family, right, so...

13:26.540 --> 13:28.473
You're not family yet either,
Rachel, so...

13:28.475 --> 13:30.341
We're getting married on Sunday.

13:30.343 --> 13:31.376
Can I see him?

13:31.378 --> 13:33.328
Unfortunately,
you can't just yet.

13:33.329 --> 13:35.279
The police want to talk to him
when he wakes up.
Police?

13:35.282 --> 13:37.382
They were thrown off an airplane
on the tarmac.

13:37.384 --> 13:38.483
The other guys are in jail.

13:38.484 --> 13:39.583
You idiots couldn't make it
through a two-hour flight

13:39.586 --> 13:41.036
without getting hammered?

13:41.037 --> 13:42.487
This is all going to work out.

13:42.489 --> 13:46.124
Really, Matt? We're getting
married in Mexico in two days.

13:46.126 --> 13:47.492
Half the wedding party
is in jail,

13:47.494 --> 13:49.594
and my fiancé is unconscious.

13:49.596 --> 13:51.529
How exactly is that
gonna work out?

13:51.531 --> 13:53.531
[ Groans ]

13:53.532 --> 13:55.532
I saw "the lion king" when
it came to L.A. last year.

13:55.535 --> 13:56.935
Were you in the show?

13:56.937 --> 14:00.271
He was.
And the 17 years before that.

14:00.273 --> 14:02.607
[ Chuckles ] Lawrence has been
mufasa since the very beginning.

14:02.609 --> 14:05.276
And he gets better every year.

14:05.278 --> 14:08.046
I've seen you perform
four times, Lawrence.

14:08.048 --> 14:11.449
I brought my son to see you
every time you came to L.A.

14:11.451 --> 14:13.852
The first time
we came to see the show,

14:13.854 --> 14:17.555
he begged for a pet lion
for months.

14:17.557 --> 14:22.493
So finally, my husband took
our poor dog to the groomer...

14:22.495 --> 14:23.528
No.

14:23.530 --> 14:24.963
Mm-hmm.
[ Both chuckle ]

14:24.965 --> 14:27.498
And one very tolerant
labradoodle

14:27.500 --> 14:29.901
became our very own mufasa.

14:29.903 --> 14:31.135
[ Laughs ]

14:31.137 --> 14:34.505
How old is he now, your son?

14:38.378 --> 14:41.880
Doctor?
Is everything okay?

14:41.882 --> 14:44.415
Yes, of course it is.
Uh, I'll be right back.

14:44.417 --> 14:47.352
Malaya, can you prep
the procedure, please?

14:47.354 --> 14:49.220
Jesse: A lot of patients
here tonight.

14:49.222 --> 14:53.324
I'll be right back.
You're in good hands.

14:53.326 --> 14:55.393
¶¶

15:06.606 --> 15:10.375
When I came home
from the hospital,

15:10.377 --> 15:17.482
there was a... a box
from the police.

15:17.484 --> 15:20.652
With all of
our personal effects.

15:20.654 --> 15:23.655
And among the items was...

15:23.657 --> 15:25.490
That cd.

15:25.492 --> 15:29.427
"The lion king" cast recording.

15:29.429 --> 15:37.429
We must have listened to it, oh,
maybe a few thousand times.

15:38.071 --> 15:41.506
And then it got lost.

15:41.508 --> 15:44.475
The accident must have
shook it loose.

15:44.477 --> 15:47.712
[ Voice breaking ]
Sometimes I think I'm being
punished, and I don't know why.

15:47.714 --> 15:49.280
[ Exhales sharply ]

15:52.619 --> 15:55.954
Listen to me closely.

15:57.557 --> 16:00.725
[ Inhales ]

16:00.727 --> 16:04.228
[ Off-key ]
¶ nants ¶

16:04.230 --> 16:11.402
¶ ingonyama bagithi baba ¶

16:11.404 --> 16:16.641
¶ ingonyama ¶

16:17.444 --> 16:19.610
I'm still working on the lyrics.

16:19.612 --> 16:22.113
[ Laughs ]

16:24.217 --> 16:26.317
[ Laughs ]

16:26.319 --> 16:29.087
Paul, why are you here?
You should be at the store.

16:32.192 --> 16:33.658
Uncle Paul died when I was 5.

16:33.660 --> 16:36.427
They owned a woman's-clothing
store in fullerton.

16:36.429 --> 16:38.262
20 years ago.

16:38.264 --> 16:39.630
I have to get to the store now.

16:39.632 --> 16:42.467
Dad, dad, dad.
It's me. It's Jeremy.

16:42.469 --> 16:43.735
Now lay down.

16:43.737 --> 16:47.105
It's my fault.
I... I forgot his radio.

16:47.107 --> 16:48.740
Music always soothes him.

16:48.742 --> 16:52.377
Jeremy, can Dr. Lorenson and I
talk with you privately?

16:52.379 --> 16:55.246
Dad, I'm gonna be
right over there, okay?

16:55.248 --> 16:57.482
You're gonna be able to see me
the whole time.

16:57.484 --> 17:00.084
A-all... all right.

17:06.159 --> 17:08.092
Jeremy, does your father have
a "do not resuscitate" order?

17:08.094 --> 17:10.061
No. Why?

17:10.062 --> 17:12.029
Is there anyone you can call
to join you here?

17:12.032 --> 17:13.131
Any other family?

17:13.133 --> 17:14.599
It's just me and my dad.

17:14.601 --> 17:16.634
I'm the one who gives him
his medications.

17:16.636 --> 17:18.403
I bathe him, feed him,
dress him.

17:18.405 --> 17:20.271
How old are you? 17?

17:20.273 --> 17:21.806
18.

17:21.808 --> 17:23.775
Jeremy, this is hard,

17:23.777 --> 17:27.545
but the cancer has weakened
your father's heart

17:27.547 --> 17:30.248
to the point where
it could arrest at any time.

17:30.250 --> 17:32.617
If that happens,
we have two options.

17:32.619 --> 17:34.585
We can try and get it
working again,

17:34.587 --> 17:37.789
which will be painful
and most likely unsuccessful,

17:37.791 --> 17:40.525
or we can make him
more comfortable.

17:40.527 --> 17:42.660
Comfortable?
So he can die?

17:42.662 --> 17:43.728
So he can rest.

17:43.730 --> 17:45.430
He's old and he's got cancer,

17:45.432 --> 17:47.231
so he's not worth saving, right?

17:47.233 --> 17:49.634
No, Jeremy.
I've got to go back to him.

17:50.804 --> 17:52.103
We'll get it for you.

17:52.105 --> 17:53.438
You know, it is late.

17:53.440 --> 17:55.239
You just... you just need
some rest.

17:55.241 --> 17:57.108
Well, we've... we've got
a lot of work to do.

18:01.081 --> 18:02.647
Is everything okay?
Of course.

18:02.649 --> 18:05.783
Dr. Pineda, you'll lead.

18:05.785 --> 18:07.552
Mr. falls,
open your mouth, please.

18:07.554 --> 18:08.853
This will only take a minute.

18:08.855 --> 18:10.822
Make sure you see it first.

18:10.824 --> 18:13.291
I see it.

18:13.292 --> 18:15.759
And steadily advance
into the abscess wall.

18:15.762 --> 18:18.229
[ Hissing ]
We have suction.

18:18.231 --> 18:19.864
Got it.

18:19.866 --> 18:22.166
It's drained.

18:23.169 --> 18:24.702
Oh, my God.
[ Monitor alarm beeping ]

18:24.704 --> 18:25.870
Leanne: Okay,
sit him up, Jesse.

18:25.872 --> 18:26.871
What's happening?
I've got you.

18:26.873 --> 18:29.057
Okay. Okay.

18:29.058 --> 18:31.242
Dr. Pineda, get in here now.
Get back in there.

18:31.244 --> 18:32.743
We got you.
It's gonna be okay.

18:33.813 --> 18:36.314
Did I hit the carotid?

18:36.316 --> 18:38.382
Get in here, Dr. Pineda, now.
Dr. Pineda!

18:44.324 --> 18:45.456
[ Gagging ]
Please do something.

18:45.458 --> 18:46.424
Dr. Pineda,
get in here now.

18:46.426 --> 18:48.626
Gauze and pressure, please.

18:48.628 --> 18:50.161
[ Gagging ]

18:50.163 --> 18:51.362
Should we intubate?

18:51.364 --> 18:53.664
Should we, Dr. Pineda?

18:53.666 --> 18:57.602
No signs of expanding hematoma.

18:57.604 --> 18:59.904
Airway is opened.
No intubation.

18:59.906 --> 19:02.406
I agree. Lawrence,
just try to relax.

19:02.408 --> 19:03.741
That puncture of the carotid

19:03.743 --> 19:06.611
should seal itself
in just a moment.

19:06.613 --> 19:08.813
Pull the gauze out and check.

19:08.815 --> 19:11.249
It's stopping.

19:11.251 --> 19:12.750
You okay?
[ Grunts ]

19:14.454 --> 19:15.920
[ Wheezes ]

19:19.159 --> 19:21.492
Can you wait?

19:21.494 --> 19:23.928
All she does is worry
when she's awake.

19:23.930 --> 19:25.863
It's better if she sleeps
till my dad's out of surgery.

19:25.865 --> 19:27.932
Yeah, I'll give her another 20.

19:30.637 --> 19:33.204
What you did was
pretty incredible.

19:33.206 --> 19:35.673
I wish
everybody would just stop.

19:35.675 --> 19:37.808
I get it.

19:37.810 --> 19:41.779
You think because you waited,
bad things happened.

19:41.781 --> 19:42.947
That's a fact.

19:42.949 --> 19:46.617
I don't know.
I wasn't there.

19:46.619 --> 19:49.220
But I do know what a broken bone
feels like.

19:49.222 --> 19:51.722
I know what a dislocated hip
feels like.

19:54.961 --> 19:56.794
You were dead.

19:56.796 --> 19:58.863
You were all dead.

19:58.865 --> 20:00.698
Except you jumped out
that window

20:00.700 --> 20:02.833
and you dragged yourself
through unimaginable pain

20:02.835 --> 20:05.603
to get help.

20:05.605 --> 20:07.872
<i>That</i> is a fact.

20:15.882 --> 20:17.732
There's gonna be times

20:17.733 --> 20:19.583
when there's nobody there
to back you up,

20:19.586 --> 20:20.718
when the only thing you have

20:20.720 --> 20:23.487
is your eyes and your instincts.

20:23.489 --> 20:26.824
It's important
that you trust yourself.

20:26.826 --> 20:31.829
And never, ever, ever give up
on the patient.

20:31.831 --> 20:33.764
No matter what.

20:38.304 --> 20:39.904
[ Sighs ]

20:39.906 --> 20:40.972
Neal.

20:40.974 --> 20:44.842
What do we do about Jeremy?

20:44.844 --> 20:46.844
We respect his wishes.
He has all the facts.

20:46.846 --> 20:48.713
There's more to this decision
than just facts.

20:48.715 --> 20:49.814
I should talk to him again.

20:49.816 --> 20:51.616
You know, it's not our job

20:51.618 --> 20:53.918
to convince them
to d.N.R. A loved one.

20:53.920 --> 20:55.953
We can't pretend
to know what it's like

20:55.955 --> 20:57.788
to be faced
with that kind of decision.

20:57.790 --> 20:59.023
I don't have to pretend.

21:04.664 --> 21:07.298
I've been where he is.
I can talk to him.

21:07.300 --> 21:08.300
Okay.

21:08.301 --> 21:10.368
But be careful.

21:17.710 --> 21:18.943
Woman: Thank you, ma'am.

21:22.015 --> 21:23.514
So, you're the new Taylor?

21:23.516 --> 21:26.050
In a manner of speaking, sure.

21:26.052 --> 21:28.286
Brooklyn?
I want to say, uh, red hook.

21:28.288 --> 21:30.021
Carroll gardens.
Very good.

21:30.023 --> 21:32.790
Nice. Finally, someone
from my neck of the woods.

21:32.792 --> 21:34.558
Sorry, I'm Mario...
Savetti.

21:34.560 --> 21:35.893
The long shot.
What?

21:35.895 --> 21:37.829
Don't take it personally.

21:37.830 --> 21:39.764
I have to learn a lot of names
very quickly.

21:39.766 --> 21:41.032
So that's how I remember you.

21:41.034 --> 21:44.018
The long shot?

21:44.019 --> 21:47.003
The least likely person to get
here, and yet here you are.

21:47.006 --> 21:48.039
Mazel tov.

21:48.041 --> 21:49.473
Have you met Dr. Hudson?

21:49.475 --> 21:51.042
Neal.
Prince charming.

21:51.044 --> 21:53.811
Uh, why do I get "long shot" and
he gets "prince charming"?

21:53.813 --> 21:56.047
Well, I mean, look at him.

21:56.049 --> 21:57.515
Nice to meet you.

22:00.753 --> 22:03.988
Is he okay?

22:03.990 --> 22:05.306
He's just sleeping.

22:05.307 --> 22:06.623
Maybe you should
check him again.

22:06.626 --> 22:08.993
He's fine.
I promise.

22:12.832 --> 22:15.766
What?
What is it?

22:17.370 --> 22:19.637
These marks around your eyes.

22:19.639 --> 22:22.406
The other doctor
already checked me.

22:23.676 --> 22:26.777
My son jumped out of a window,

22:26.779 --> 22:30.481
and nobody will tell me if my
husband is going to live or die.

22:30.483 --> 22:33.517
They're really
all I care about right now.

22:33.519 --> 22:36.120
I understand.

22:36.122 --> 22:38.089
I'll, uh,
see what I can find out.

22:43.629 --> 22:46.530
Hey, what did you find in
Karen Irving's trauma survey?

22:46.532 --> 22:47.949
Checking up on me now?

22:47.950 --> 22:49.367
No, I'm checking up on<i> her.</i>

22:49.369 --> 22:50.602
Why?
I'm not sure.

22:50.603 --> 22:52.243
Do you mind if I take a look
at her chart?

22:54.140 --> 22:56.574
You didn't order a c.T.A.
Of her head and neck?

22:56.576 --> 22:58.126
Why would I do that?

22:58.127 --> 22:59.677
She has some bruising
around the eyes.

22:59.679 --> 23:00.711
She got tossed around a lot.

23:00.713 --> 23:02.646
A few bruises
aren't worth a c.T.A.

23:02.648 --> 23:05.082
It just looks strange to me.

23:05.083 --> 23:07.517
Should I code "looks strange to
Angus" on the insurance form?

23:07.520 --> 23:09.053
[ Scoffs ]

23:09.055 --> 23:10.988
A c.T.A. Is not indicated.

23:10.989 --> 23:12.922
I think you're wrong.
Not your patient, man.

23:15.461 --> 23:17.762
I looked up our new director,
Gina perello.

23:17.764 --> 23:19.597
Yale, Columbia,

23:19.598 --> 23:21.431
headed up an E.R. in sacramento,
same hospital group,

23:21.434 --> 23:22.933
and she ran
about a dozen marathons.

23:22.935 --> 23:25.286
You're stalking.

23:25.287 --> 23:27.638
She's the new boss.
That's all you need to know.

23:27.640 --> 23:30.574
It doesn't bother you
they didn't give
the job to Dr. Rorish?

23:30.576 --> 23:32.143
She would never want that job.

23:32.145 --> 23:35.713
Well, what about Guthrie?
He's been here since dial-up.

23:35.715 --> 23:38.482
Dial-up
wasn't that long ago.

23:43.055 --> 23:45.990
<i>[ Indistinct talking
over P.A. ]</i>

23:50.696 --> 23:53.464
[ Police radio chatter ]

23:55.168 --> 23:57.568
People come out here
for three reasons...

23:57.570 --> 23:59.904
To think about mistakes
they've already made

23:59.906 --> 24:02.072
or the one
that they're about to make.

24:02.074 --> 24:04.208
You know, that's only two.

24:04.210 --> 24:06.043
Smoke break is number three.

24:06.045 --> 24:08.813
But your mama knows
he taught you better than that.

24:08.815 --> 24:10.815
[ Sighs ]

24:10.817 --> 24:14.084
What if two doctors disagree
on how to treat a patient?

24:14.086 --> 24:18.522
That's an age-old question
in this place.

24:18.524 --> 24:20.825
For a senior doc,
it's more complicated.

24:20.827 --> 24:23.194
For a resident, it's simple.

24:23.196 --> 24:25.229
You don't know enough
to sit on it.

24:25.231 --> 24:27.932
So you have to tell
an attending.

24:27.934 --> 24:30.067
What patient
are you talking about?

24:32.738 --> 24:34.972
It's the mom
from the home invasion.

24:34.974 --> 24:37.091
Karen Irving.

24:37.092 --> 24:39.209
She has bruising under her eyes.

24:39.212 --> 24:40.177
What kind of bruising?

24:40.179 --> 24:41.212
I think it's petechiae.

24:41.214 --> 24:42.214
That's Mario's patient.

24:42.215 --> 24:45.249
He doesn't agree.

24:45.251 --> 24:46.851
But you're pretty sure
you're right.

24:46.853 --> 24:48.252
Yeah, and I won't be sure
without a c.T.A.

24:48.254 --> 24:52.556
That's a good thing,
'cause you just ordered one.

24:52.558 --> 24:53.791
Excuse me?

24:53.793 --> 24:55.693
Dr. Leighton, I'm a nurse.

24:55.695 --> 24:57.761
I take my orders from doctors,
capiche?

24:57.763 --> 24:59.146
No, no.

24:59.147 --> 25:00.530
No, no.
I-i-i can't do that.

25:00.533 --> 25:02.166
If it comes back clean,
it's our secret.

25:02.168 --> 25:05.102
If not,
you just saved two lives.

25:05.104 --> 25:06.504
Two?

25:06.506 --> 25:09.507
The patient
and Dr. Savetti.

25:13.613 --> 25:15.679
[ Indistinct talking ]

25:17.817 --> 25:19.267
Hey.

25:19.268 --> 25:20.718
The nurses told me
you were out here.

25:20.720 --> 25:21.720
Is my father okay?

25:21.721 --> 25:24.088
He's fine.
He's sleeping.

25:24.090 --> 25:27.157
[ Sighs ] I know
what you're gonna say.

25:27.159 --> 25:28.526
Every time we end up
in a hospital,

25:28.528 --> 25:30.160
someone tells me
it's time to let him go.

25:32.064 --> 25:34.965
My ex-husband told me the same
thing when our son was sick.

25:34.967 --> 25:41.772
After two very painful years,
he died.

25:41.774 --> 25:44.975
I couldn't even
look at my husband.

25:44.977 --> 25:47.778
Not because I was angry
that he'd given up,

25:47.780 --> 25:53.083
but because I couldn't face
that he may have been right.

25:56.923 --> 26:00.691
Not a day goes by
that I don't wonder

26:00.693 --> 26:04.828
[sighs] If I made my son
work too hard to die.

26:04.830 --> 26:09.133
I'm sorry that happened to you.

26:09.135 --> 26:10.334
I really am.

26:11.904 --> 26:13.304
But I promised him.

26:13.306 --> 26:15.573
You promised who?

26:15.575 --> 26:17.575
My father.

26:18.911 --> 26:20.244
When he realized
what was happening,

26:20.246 --> 26:22.980
he told me
I'd have to grow up fast

26:22.982 --> 26:26.016
and be the man of the house now.

26:26.018 --> 26:28.352
I promised him I would.

26:28.354 --> 26:30.588
I can't break that promise.

26:30.590 --> 26:34.191
I have to fight for him.

26:37.697 --> 26:38.829
[ Monitor alarm beeping ]

26:38.831 --> 26:40.798
Dr. Leighton,
your bachelor is seizing.

26:40.800 --> 26:42.866
[ Grunting ]

26:42.868 --> 26:43.801
Heart rate's 220.

26:43.803 --> 26:45.135
Roll him.

26:46.205 --> 26:47.205
Start suction.

26:48.040 --> 26:50.240
This doesn't make sense.

26:50.242 --> 26:52.309
He just had a hangover.

27:00.186 --> 27:01.852
Yeah, well, give me an e.T.A.,
all right?

27:01.854 --> 27:03.921
Call me back.
I'm in trauma 1.

27:07.994 --> 27:10.794
Where's my son?

27:12.331 --> 27:13.364
I'm here, dad.

27:16.836 --> 27:20.771
When the warranty runs out,

27:20.773 --> 27:23.874
you have to get rid of the car.

27:23.876 --> 27:26.310
That's what we used to say.

27:28.681 --> 27:29.713
Can you sit forward for me?

27:29.715 --> 27:31.849
[ Groans ]
Dad.

27:31.851 --> 27:33.083
There we are.

27:34.687 --> 27:35.719
Jeremy.

27:35.721 --> 27:39.890
Yes?
It's me, dad.

27:39.892 --> 27:40.858
It's Jeremy.

27:40.860 --> 27:42.893
What's my name?

27:42.895 --> 27:47.698
Your name is Edwin, dad.
Edwin Mercer.

27:56.008 --> 28:01.111
Will you tell Jeremy
his father is looking for him?

28:05.017 --> 28:07.384
I will.

28:07.386 --> 28:08.952
I'll tell him.

28:10.256 --> 28:12.723
Aaron had a heart attack.
I need to know everything.

28:12.725 --> 28:14.858
It's the only way
I'm gonna be able to help him.

28:14.860 --> 28:18.028
He drank too much.
That's... I swear that's all...

28:18.030 --> 28:19.697
We don't have time for this!
Do you get it?

28:19.699 --> 28:21.865
He is going to die.
I need the truth now.

28:21.867 --> 28:24.702
It's cocaine.

28:24.704 --> 28:27.771
Aaron packed it in a condom.
He said it would work.

28:27.773 --> 28:29.306
Are you saying he swallowed it?

28:29.307 --> 28:30.840
We thought it would just...
Thank you.

28:30.843 --> 28:31.809
Go through him.

28:31.811 --> 28:32.811
It was for our honeymoon!

28:32.812 --> 28:34.244
Are you insane?!

28:34.246 --> 28:36.213
You turned Aaron
into a drug mule?!

28:37.817 --> 28:40.150
Rachel!

28:41.187 --> 28:43.420
I need an endoscope
at center stage, now!

28:46.792 --> 28:49.460
[ Defibrillator paddles
buzzing ]

28:50.496 --> 28:52.830
I have your c.T.A. Results
on Karen Irving.

28:52.832 --> 28:54.364
I didn't order a c.T.A.
On Karen.

28:54.366 --> 28:56.467
Dr. Savetti!
I need you here now!

28:56.469 --> 28:58.119
What is it?

28:58.120 --> 28:59.770
Fireworks. He and his friends
set them off.

28:59.772 --> 29:00.504
Container impaled him.

29:00.506 --> 29:01.889
It was a rocket.

29:01.890 --> 29:03.273
[ Chuckling ]
We used black powder.

29:03.275 --> 29:04.808
Get it out, man.
It hurts.

29:04.810 --> 29:06.777
Page Cole Guthrie, please.

29:06.779 --> 29:07.878
His pressure's down.

29:07.880 --> 29:08.880
Do something.

29:08.881 --> 29:10.247
Risa,
I need a central-line kit.

29:10.249 --> 29:12.883
Dr. Lorenson,
over here, please.

29:12.885 --> 29:15.052
He needs levophed,
possibly a second pressor.

29:15.054 --> 29:16.220
This is severe sepsis.

29:16.222 --> 29:18.039
Wh-what's sepsis?

29:18.040 --> 29:19.857
Sepsis is like
bacteria eating holes

29:19.859 --> 29:21.425
into every millimeter
of his blood vessels,

29:21.427 --> 29:24.394
causing the fluid to leak out.

29:24.396 --> 29:25.863
[ Voice breaking ]
Is it painful?

29:25.865 --> 29:27.397
It is.

29:34.206 --> 29:36.206
Mario, I'm the only boss
that matters.

29:36.208 --> 29:37.841
Totally.

29:37.842 --> 29:39.475
I was pulled out of surgery
on a stabbing for this.

29:39.478 --> 29:41.945
It better be good.
Foreign object in his abdomen,

29:41.947 --> 29:43.580
positive blood in morison's.

29:43.581 --> 29:45.214
May have perforated his liver.
Is that good enough for you?

29:45.217 --> 29:46.784
B.P. Is dropping.
Now 80/50.

29:46.786 --> 29:48.152
He's in shock.
What's our access?

29:48.154 --> 29:49.520
Just a peripheral
from the field.

29:49.522 --> 29:51.455
They can place a central line
in a second, though.

29:51.457 --> 29:53.123
We'll take it from here.
I want a thermal cordis

29:53.125 --> 29:54.708
while the E.R.
patches him up for the O.R.

29:54.709 --> 29:56.292
Copy that.
And nobody touch the firework.

29:56.295 --> 29:59.296
Dr. Guthrie, our residents
handle procedures down here.

29:59.298 --> 30:00.898
Mario, central line, now.

30:00.900 --> 30:03.534
It's surgical management now.
I'm the attending.

30:03.536 --> 30:05.803
You're the surgical attending...
In trauma 1.

30:05.805 --> 30:08.272
Maybe this isn't the time
for interdepartmental warfare.

30:08.274 --> 30:09.623
We're all on the same team.

30:09.624 --> 30:10.973
Couldn't agree more,
Dr. Hudson.

30:10.976 --> 30:13.877
Frank Irving's upstairs
on his 22nd unit of blood.

30:13.879 --> 30:15.312
I'd like to get back to him
before he flatlines.

30:15.314 --> 30:16.947
Done!
Done!

30:16.949 --> 30:20.984
Let's run the fluids
and get this guy upstairs.

30:20.986 --> 30:22.252
Now can I take my patient?

30:22.254 --> 30:23.353
All yours.

30:23.355 --> 30:24.922
Dr. Hudson,
I've now got two criticals

30:24.924 --> 30:26.323
and I'm all out of surgeons.

30:26.325 --> 30:27.958
I could use your help upstairs.

30:27.960 --> 30:29.543
I'm not a surgeon.
I'm an E.R. doc.

30:29.544 --> 30:31.127
We're all on the same team,
right?
[ Monitor alarm beeping ]

30:31.130 --> 30:32.062
Pete:
Someone help my mom!

30:32.064 --> 30:33.497
Someone help my mom!

30:33.499 --> 30:34.865
All right, all right.
We're gonna take care of her.

30:34.866 --> 30:36.232
What's happening to her?!
I'm gonna turn you over here.

30:36.235 --> 30:37.568
Mom, are you okay?
Why is she seizing?

30:37.570 --> 30:40.270
She's your patient, Savetti.
You tell me.

30:42.408 --> 30:44.041
Dr. Hudson, are you coming,

30:44.043 --> 30:47.010
or did we just stabilize
this kid for nothing?

30:47.012 --> 30:48.846
Dr. Pineda,
I need you over here, please.

30:48.848 --> 30:50.347
Assist Dr. Lorenson
with the pressors.

30:50.349 --> 30:51.448
Page me if there's any change.

30:51.450 --> 30:53.050
Clear the way.
Gurney coming through!

30:55.487 --> 30:56.920
Clear the way!

30:58.958 --> 31:00.490
Yeah. Okay.
Got it?

31:00.492 --> 31:03.594
Yeah.
All right, careful now.

31:03.596 --> 31:04.494
Do you smell that?

31:04.496 --> 31:06.997
[ Fizzling ]

31:06.999 --> 31:09.066
Smoke.
This firework's still live.

31:16.342 --> 31:17.342
Neal: I need water!

31:17.343 --> 31:18.275
May I?

31:18.277 --> 31:19.877
Is that smoke?

31:19.879 --> 31:21.578
I need another O.R.
and another trauma attending.

31:21.580 --> 31:23.447
We're full!
Page the trauma fellow
on backup call.

31:23.449 --> 31:25.609
In the meantime, I'm taking him
into the stabbing room.

31:27.486 --> 31:29.286
[ Monitor alarms beeping ]
Dr. Leighton, facemask, please.

31:29.288 --> 31:30.648
Mama, where's that ativan?
Line in.

31:31.457 --> 31:32.623
Slam it.

31:35.461 --> 31:39.129
[ Beeping stops ]
Dr. Rorish, I think she has
petechiae around her eyes.

31:39.131 --> 31:40.264
When did you first spot it?

31:40.266 --> 31:41.198
A couple hours ago.

31:41.199 --> 31:42.131
And you didn't do anything?

31:42.134 --> 31:44.334
I ordered a c.T.A.

31:44.336 --> 31:45.502
Then why didn't you
act on the results?

31:45.504 --> 31:48.038
They haven't come back yet.

31:48.039 --> 31:50.573
It's up to you to fight
for your patient, Dr. Savetti.

31:50.576 --> 31:51.475
How many units?

31:51.477 --> 31:52.509
We just hung number 30.

31:52.511 --> 31:54.311
30? Okay,
I need to get in.

31:54.313 --> 31:56.480
Dr. Hudson, help my team
with the firework.

31:56.482 --> 31:57.514
Suction here, please.

31:57.516 --> 31:58.548
Clamp here, please.

31:58.550 --> 32:00.384
Another 0 silk.

32:00.386 --> 32:01.685
Kelley clamp, please.
[ Monitor alarm beeping ]

32:01.687 --> 32:03.353
His blood pressure's
bottoming out.
Why?

32:03.355 --> 32:05.222
I don't know.
I don't know.

32:05.224 --> 32:07.491
This required
a complex dissection.

32:07.493 --> 32:09.159
You just pulled it.
Wrong move.

32:09.161 --> 32:09.993
Let me in, please.

32:09.995 --> 32:11.778
So what's your plan?

32:11.779 --> 32:13.562
He's bleeding from his
inferior epigastric artery.

32:13.565 --> 32:15.565
His wound didn't violate
his rectus sheath.

32:15.567 --> 32:18.068
It's just
a highly vascular spot.

32:19.104 --> 32:20.404
Suction, please.

32:20.406 --> 32:22.406
[ Hissing ]

32:22.408 --> 32:26.610
Tying off
the inferior epigastric branch.

32:28.447 --> 32:29.646
Done.
Hemostasis.

32:29.648 --> 32:31.832
Impressive.

32:31.833 --> 32:34.017
I don't see any
abdominal violation here.

32:34.019 --> 32:35.652
[ Cellphone vibrating ]
Lucky guy.

32:35.653 --> 32:37.286
Dr. Spencer,
assist Dr. Hudson as he closes.

32:37.289 --> 32:40.123
I can't close. I've got
a patient crumping downstairs.

32:40.125 --> 32:41.959
Doctor?

32:41.961 --> 32:44.161
You know I'm gonna have
to steal you from leanne, right?

32:45.497 --> 32:49.633
Let's get her comfortable and
get her upstairs for a head ct.

32:49.635 --> 32:51.268
Mama,
when Mrs. Irving comes back,

32:51.270 --> 32:53.537
can you make sure that she's
someplace away from her son

32:53.539 --> 32:55.639
so that she and I have
a chance to speak?

32:55.641 --> 32:57.741
Understood.
Thanks.

32:57.743 --> 33:02.646
You two have some stuff
to figure out.

33:05.651 --> 33:07.451
I get it.

33:07.453 --> 33:09.019
Lucky the patient didn't die.

33:09.021 --> 33:11.188
You're not lucky.
<i>She</i> is.

33:15.594 --> 33:17.427
[ Monitor alarm beeping ]
Dr. Hudson, my dad!

33:17.429 --> 33:18.579
[ Edwin coughing ]

33:18.580 --> 33:19.730
He just started coughing
for no reason.

33:19.732 --> 33:22.699
[ Coughing continues ]
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

33:22.701 --> 33:24.101
It's okay, it's okay.

33:24.103 --> 33:25.702
There's literally no exchange.

33:25.704 --> 33:27.237
It's all fluid.

33:27.239 --> 33:28.822
Should we take him off saline?

33:28.823 --> 33:30.406
No, keep it running.
What's happening?

33:30.409 --> 33:32.275
His lungs are filled with fluid.

33:32.277 --> 33:33.744
Check again.
Check the X-Ray.

33:33.746 --> 33:36.246
Jeremy, extra tests won't change
what we already know.

33:36.248 --> 33:37.659
Well, if there's fluid
in his lungs,

33:37.660 --> 33:39.071
why are you giving him
more saline?

33:39.072 --> 33:40.483
You know,
it's an impossible situation.

33:40.486 --> 33:42.286
His heart's failing.

33:42.287 --> 33:44.087
If we withhold fluids,
then he'll die from
his low blood pressure.

33:44.089 --> 33:45.789
But if we push fluids...

33:45.791 --> 33:47.791
He'll drown in his own lungs.

33:58.737 --> 34:00.303
What made you think
it was petechiae?

34:02.041 --> 34:05.409
Because those guys
separated them.

34:05.411 --> 34:08.578
Why separate them unless...

34:13.118 --> 34:15.185
Oh, man.
Yeah.

34:15.187 --> 34:17.154
[ Pouring coffee ]

34:20.159 --> 34:25.429
Your seizing was very likely
caused by anoxic brain injury.

34:25.431 --> 34:26.696
The damage isn't permanent.

34:26.698 --> 34:29.399
Thank you.

34:29.401 --> 34:32.369
Um, can you tell me
how my husband is doing?

34:32.371 --> 34:35.505
He's still critical.

34:35.507 --> 34:38.075
But, Karen,
we should talk about you.

34:40.412 --> 34:45.348
The little red marks on
your face are called petechiae.

34:45.350 --> 34:48.785
They're tiny bruises
that indicate strangulation.

34:48.787 --> 34:51.621
It's something that we look for

34:51.623 --> 34:53.390
when there's a chance
of sexual assault.

35:00.799 --> 35:03.433
Karen...

35:03.435 --> 35:05.735
What happened to you?

35:08.173 --> 35:12.676
They separated us
from the beginning.

35:12.678 --> 35:16.313
One of them
brought me into the kitchen,

35:16.315 --> 35:18.882
pushed me into the pantry,

35:18.884 --> 35:22.853
and he put his hands
around my neck.

35:26.291 --> 35:30.627
I thought I was gonna die.

35:30.629 --> 35:35.732
But I knew if he was hurting me,
then he wasn't hurting them.

35:39.705 --> 35:43.406
They can't ever know.

35:43.408 --> 35:45.709
Frank and Pete.

35:45.711 --> 35:47.744
You can never tell them.

35:49.281 --> 35:51.648
Karen...

35:51.650 --> 35:53.550
Your husband and your son

35:53.552 --> 35:56.920
are some of the strongest people
I've ever met.

35:56.922 --> 35:58.588
And so are you.

36:08.901 --> 36:10.767
What happened?

36:10.769 --> 36:12.869
You freaking scared the crap
out of us is what happened.

36:12.871 --> 36:14.437
Aaron, you had a heart attack.

36:14.439 --> 36:16.940
The cocaine
that you swallowed leaked

36:16.942 --> 36:18.942
